# AI Image Prediction Flask Application

This Flask application provides a web interface for users to upload images and receive AI predictions about the content of those images. It also includes a chatbot feature that users can interact with for help.

## Features

- Image upload via drag-and-drop or file browser
- AI prediction results displayed as a list
- Chatbot assistance via a popup interface
- Clean, responsive UI design

## Requirements

- Python 3.10+
- Flask
- Werkzeug

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
```
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ai-image-prediction.git
cd Skin_cancer
```

2. Create a virtual environment (recommended):
```
python -m venv venv
```

3. Activate the virtual environment:
   - On Windows:
   ```
   venv\Scripts\activate
   ```
   - On macOS/Linux:
   ```
   source venv/bin/activate
   ```

4. Install the required dependencies:
```
pip install flask
```

## Project Structure

```
ai-image-prediction/
├── app.py                  # Flask application
├── static/                 # Static files
│   └── uploads/            # Uploaded images folder
│   └── model               # Model segmentation
└── templates/              # HTML templates
    └── index.html          # Main application template
```

## Running the Application

1. Ensure your virtual environment is activated
2. Run the Flask application:
```
python app.py
```
3. Open your web browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:5000/

